    "project-results": "Project Results:",
    "project-novel-eval-problem-title": "Core Problem:",
    "project-novel-eval-problem": "Fiction evaluation is subjective, fragmented, and difficult to standardize: editors often rely on experience, platform intuition, genre familiarity, and market judgment that are hard to reuse or compare across works. This project explores whether LLM Rubric can turn that editor-like judgment into explicit, interpretable, and iteratively improvable evaluation criteria without reducing fiction assessment to a single opaque score.",
    "project-novel-eval-solution-title": "System Workflow:",
    "project-novel-eval-solution": "I built a local single-user evaluation system around a staged LLM Rubric workflow: input screening and analysis-mode selection, type classification, 8-axis rubric scoring, type-specific lens evaluation, consistency checks, aggregation, and final projection into a concise result format. Beyond the rubric design itself, the project also implements the engineering workflow around it, including a web interface for task creation and result review, a FastAPI backend for task execution, SQLite persistence for history and results, prompt assets, schema validation, and eval/batch tooling for regression checks.",
    "project-mental-background": "Traditional mental health assessment relies on subjective questionnaires with intermittent evaluation issues and subjective biases. With the proliferation of wearable devices enabling continuous physiological monitoring, the project aims to build a mental health assessment model based on wearable device data to achieve objective, continuous mental state monitoring, providing new technical approaches for mental health evaluation.",
    "project-mental-implementation": "Selected 43 key variables from 4-year NetHealth observational data to construct a multi-time scale dataset of approximately 30k entries; applied Multiple Imputation by Chained Equations (MICE) for missing values, used Boxplot to detect and remove outliers, implemented BoxCox transformation for skewed data, used PCA for dimensionality reduction on highly multicollinear original time series data; built ElasticNet, RandomForest, XGBoost base models, employed decision tree-based Stacking ensemble strategy, and ultimately optimized overall hyperparameters through grid search.",
    "project-mental-results": "The ensemble model achieved excellent performance with MSE 0.032, significantly outperforming all base models; successfully enabled end-to-end prediction from wearable device data to mental health status; the project received national innovation training program funding and was completed in May 2024, providing a new technical pathway for mental health monitoring.",
    "project-health-title": "Public Health Metrics in Modern China",
    "project-health-desc": "National Statistical Modeling Competition",
    "project-health-background": "With the accelerating modernization process, traditional single health indicators cannot comprehensively reflect the complex health status changes of Chinese residents. This project aims to build a comprehensive health evaluation system to multi-dimensionally assess people's health status and influencing factors, providing data support for public health policy in the context of modernization.",
    "project-health-implementation": "Integrated multi-source health indicators from National Bureau of Statistics databases and commercial databases, used web scraping to obtain medical research focus trends from CNKI; applied principal component analysis to process health indicators obtained from the database, selected the top two principal components with practical meaning as health measures based on coefficient interpretability; built LASSO regression model, used grid search to find optimal balance between coefficient sparsity and model R², ensuring model interpretability and predictive power.",
    "project-health-results": "The final model achieved excellent fitting performance with R² of approximately 0.89, successfully identifying key factors affecting Chinese residents' health status; the constructed health measurement system provides new perspectives for health assessment in the modernization process and ultimately won the first prize in the regional competition.",
