    "paper-overview-content": "This study employs interpretable machine learning methods (SHAP and PDP) to construct a random forest model, deeply analyzing PTSD influencing factors among 903 emergency responders. The research reveals that psychological resilience serves as a core protective factor with significant buffering effects on PTSD (SHAP value 0.5061). The study also identifies non-linear patterns including U-shaped age effects. Through Friedman H-statistic validation of resilience-age/trauma exposure interaction effects, differentiated intervention strategies for young and elderly emergency personnel are proposed. The findings provide data-driven decision-making evidence for PTSD prevention in high-risk occupational groups, highlighting the application value of interpretable AI in mental health.",
